<H3> <TI>   Reactions to Markiewicz Ouster Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0203190794 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1700 
GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0203190794 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] [Announcer] In the view of Jaroslaw Kaczynski, 
chairman of the Center Alliance [PC], President Lech Walesa's 
decision on the recall of the chairman of the National Radio and 
Television Broadcasting Council [KRRiT], Marek Markiewicz, lacks 
any legal basis. The leader of the Conservative Party [PK], 
Aleksander Hall, has also protested against the method of 
dismissal of Marek Markiewicz. He feels that the activities of 
the president are, regardless of his intentions, such as to 
bring disturbance into the public life of the country and to 
favor destabilization. 
  The press spokesman of the Constitutional Tribunal, Adam 
Jankiewicz, has reported that the tribnunal may consider an 
application on the matter of the determination of a ruling on 
the decision of President Lech Walesa on the recall of the 
chairman of KRRiT over a period of at least two weeks from its 
being received by the tribunal. 

