<F P=100> ALBANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Court Issues Verdicts in Secrets Case </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0103071194 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1900 
GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0103071194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana TVSH Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Albanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Tirana District Court spokesman reports that 
the trial of Romeo Lici, Martin Leka, Bashkim Feta, and 
Aleksander Frangaj, charged with conspiring to reveal state 
secrets, defined by Articles 122 and 134 of the Penal Code, 
ended today. At the end of the trial, the judicial body decided 
as follows: 
  To declare the defendants Romeo Lici and Martin Leka guilty, 
charged with the criminal act of revealing state secrets, 
anticipated by Articles 122 and 13 of the Penal Code, and to 
sentence them to four years and 18 months imprisonment, 
respectively. 
  The defendant Bashkim Feta was declared guilty for the 
criminal act of having a careless attitude while on duty, 
anticipated by Article 108 of the Penal Code, and was convicted 
with the preimprisonment term. 
  Regarding Aleksander Frangaj, the court decided to suspend 
investigations for lack of elements of the crime motive. 

</TEXT>

