Language: <F P=105> Hungarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Hungarian Government is to grant Hungarian 
Radio a special fund [celtamogatas] of 105 million forints, 
earmarked for wage increases and severance pay, [Government 
Spokeswoman] Judit Juhasz has confirmed. 
  The spokeswoman said that the government had passed special 
decrees on the legal status of public employees at Hungarian 
Radio, Hungarian Television, and the Hungarian Telegraphic 
Agency [MTI]. People can be appointed to leading positions only 
for five years in all three institutions. [passage omitted] 

