<H3> <TI>   Serbs Refuse UN Battalion Access to Srebrenica </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0403122994 Hilversum Radio Netherlands in English 1130 GMT 
4 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0403122994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hilversum Radio Netherlands </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bosnian Serb authorities are refusing to allow a 
convoy of the Dutch United Nations battalion to get through to 
the besieged Muslim enclave of Srebrenica. The Serbs are 
protesting about the amount of military equipment, especially 
ammunition, that the Dutch troops are taking to Srebrenica. The 
Serbs are also preventing 180 Canadian troops from leaving the 
Muslim enclave. 
  The Dutch contingent is authorized to relieve the Canadian 
blue helmets under an agreement signed by several parties 
including the Bosnian Serbs. At first the takeover operation 
encountered no resistance, but in the past few days the Serbs 
have toughened their stance. 

</TEXT>

