<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN: Muslims Raped, Murdered in Banja Luka </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0403121394 Paris AFP in English 1208 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0403121394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Sarajevo, March 4 (AFP) -- Moslems are being 
raped and murdered in continued ethnic cleansing in the Serb 
city of Banja Luka in northern Bosnia, a UN spokesman said here 
Friday. 
  UN High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) spokesman Kris 
Janowski told reporters of several cases of rape and murder 
since January. He said that despite reports that some of the 
attacks were carried out by "uniformed" men, none of the cases 
had ever been followed up by the authorities. 
  "Everybody's wearing pretty much the same kind of uniform. 
We understand that they are either part of some sort of militia 
or Serb military or whoever," he said of the perpetrators. 
  He said the authorities told the UNHCR "all the time" that 
they had nothing to do with the attacks which were allegedly 
being done by criminals. "But none of these cases has ever been 
followed and no one has ever been punished so we assume that 
this is all done with the knowledge and at least the silent 
consent of the authorities. Otherwise they would do something 
to stop it." 
  Janowski said "at least five persons have been murdered 
since 
the beginning of January in Banja Luka" but he did not give 
details. 
  He added that there were "countless cases of people being 
beaten up and intimidated, the Moslem neighborhood raided by 
uniformed gangs... trying to give them the message to get out" 
and that this had "been going on for quite a while." He cited 
the case of 200 Moslems who had fled the village of Bronzani 
Majdan, not far from Banja Luka, and asked the UNHCR to get them 
out of the country. [passage omitted] 
  "We are trying to monitor the situation but it is very 
difficult," Janowski said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

