<H3> <TI>   Mladic, Rose Discuss Ways To Strengthen Peace </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0303210694 Belgrade RTB Television Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1830 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0303210694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade RTB Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Marica Lalovic from Sarajevo] </F>
  [Text] Lieutenant General Ratko Mladic, commander of the 
army of the Sr pska republic, held talks in Lukavica today with 
General Michael Rose, commander of UNPROFOR [United Nations 
Protection Forces] for the former Bosnia-Herzegovina, about 
strengthening the peace in Sarajevo. The two commanders also 
talked about further controlling the weapons in and around 
Sarajevo, particularly the Muslim weapons, as the Muslim side 
has still not fully complied with the agreement on putting its 
weapons under UNPROFOR's control. By the way, as Rasim Delic, 
commander of the so-called Muslim army, did not show up, the 
meeting of military commanders of the Serbian and Muslim armies 
that should have been held in Sarajevo today did not take place. 
Michael Rose tried to excuse Delic's failure to come to the 
meeting with his being busy establishing peace, as he put it, 
for his people in central Bosnia. 

</TEXT>

