<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Martic Denies Downed Aircraft Came From RSK </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0403123694 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 0954 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0403123694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Podgorica, 4 Mar (TANJUG) -- Milan Martic, president 
of the republic of Serb Krajina (RSK), denied in today's POBJEDA 
that the downed planes had taken off from RSK territory. 
  "It is out of the question that our planes from Udbine were 
flying over the former Bosnia-Herzegovina and the Srpska 
republic. Our own airspace is sufficient for us, and we have no 
need for any Air Force activities over those areas." 
  "We do not want to interfere in the fighting between our 
brothers from the Srpska republic and the Muslims, knowing that 
our brothers have enough strength and knowledge to resist the 
Muslims, who, particularly in recent days, have abused all 
cease-fires for new armed actions against the Serbs," Martic 
said. 
  He said that the misinformation about the RSK military 
activities over the former Bosnia-Herzegovina had originated 
from BORBA. 

</TEXT>

