<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   `No Strike' on 7 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0403121794 Warsaw PAP in Polish 1012 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0403121794 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Wroclaw, 4 Mar--At a news conference in Wroclaw 
today, Tomasz Wojcik, chairman of the Lower Silesian Solidarity 
Region, stated that there would be no strike action in Wroclaw 
on 7 March. 
  Wojcik said that if there were a strike staged at a later 
date in Wroclaw, the action would be carried out in the most 
unconventional manner, "which would cause disruption, especially 
to the authorities." Among other things, there will be 
disruption in telephone services or cuts in central heating in 
municipal offices, as well as in those institutions that provide 
services for the government. 

</TEXT>

