<H3> <TI>   Ruthenian `Shadow Cabinet' Not Recognized </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0403072894 Budapest MTI in English 1922 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0403072894 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, 3 March (MTI) -- "The Hungarian government 
does not recognize the shadow cabinet of Ruthenians in 
Subcarpathia. Nor is it prepared to receive its members in 
Budapest," Hungarian Ambassador to Ukraine Istvan Varga told 
Nikola Makarevich, first deputy foreign minister of Ukraine, in 
Kiev today. The ambassador said that the recognition of 
Ruthenians as a national minority is an internal affair of 
Ukraine. 
  The cabinet of the so-called Subcarpathian Rus was formed in 
the spring of 1993 by Ruthenians seeking independence from 
Ukraine. Hungary's law on national and ethnic minorities 
mentions the Ruthenians and Ukrainians separately, thereby 
recognizing the existence of a Ruthenian minority in Hungary. 

</TEXT>

