Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 1/3/1994 -- Four new army 
commanders have been appointed recently. Their official 
assumption of duties took place on 28 February and 1 March. The 
four officers are: Major General Eugen Badalan, Major General 
Florian Caba, Major General Nicolae Oprea, and Colonel Mihai 
Palaghia. 
  The release of the army's press bureau informs that the new 
appointments are in line with the restructuring policies of the 
Romanian Army, and have been made with the approval of Romanian 
President Ion Iliescu, commander of the Armed Forces, and on 
orders of National Defense Minister Lieutenant General Niculae 
Spiroiu. 
  The new army commanders have passed through the military 
hierarchy from the stage of platoon commander to that of 
division commander, the release shows. 

