<H3> <TI>   Significance of Zhelev-Gligorov Contacts Noted </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0303172694 Sofia BTA in English 1855 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0303172694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Nikolay Koev: "Bulgarian-Macedonian Talks"] </F>
  [Text] Skopje, March 3 (BTA) -- A Bulgarian delegation led 
by Deputy Foreign Minister Dimitur Ikonomov arrived in the 
Republic of Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia 
-- FYROM]. Today Ikonomov was received by President Kiro 
Gligorov to whom he delivered a message by Bulgarian President 
Zhelyu Zhelev. 
  The message, a reply to a recent letter by Gligorov, 
emphasizes Bulgaria's principled stand for the promotion of 
relations with Macedonia. It stresses Bulgaria's desire to 
develop with its neighbours, including the young Macedonian 
state, a policy based on mutual understanding and friendship. 
  In a special message to President Zhelev, the Macedonian 
president had thanked him for the support the Republic of 
Macedonia received from Bulgaria after Greece had imposed a 
unilateral economic embargo against it. 
  The exchange of personal messages between the presidents of 
Bulgaria and Macedonia is an important part of direct contacts 
between the state leaders of the two neighbouring countries and 
has a great significance for the regulation of bilateral 
relations. Political observers here see this fact as evidence of 
the willingness of Sofia and Skopje to promote cooperation in 
the difficult situation in the Balkans, leaving behind points of 
dispute accumulated in the past. 

</TEXT>

