<F P=100> ALBANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Flagrant' Shooting Incident on FRY Border </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0503202394 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1900 
GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0503202394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana TVSH Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Albanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A flagrant incident occurred at the border with 
Yugoslavia. The Public Order Ministry spokesman reports that at 
about 1335 today another flagrant incident happened in Pogaj 
village in Has District, near border marker D/7. 
  A Yugoslav border unit, accompanied by dogs, opened fire 
toward two Albanian children who were guarding their cow, 
without going beyond the border line, but close to it. As soon 
as the shots were heard, the commander of our border post, 
together with a soldier, left immediately. But with no warning 
at all, the Yugoslav post of Goruzhup, in former Yugoslavia, 
opened fire against our border guards, who were 100 meters away 
from the border line and approximately 350 meters away from 
their post. Soldier Saimir Pal Zefi from Mirdite District was 
wounded from these very sudden shots. 
  This is a very flagrant event because there was not even the 
slightest provocation or pretext from our part. Our member of 
the joint local commission for solving border incidents and 
representatives of EC observers mission went immediately to the 
scene of the incident. 
  The Public Order Ministry strongly protests these criminal 
and unjustifiable acts that are increasing day by day. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

