<H3> <TI>   SLD Ousts 4 for Voting Against Budget </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0503154894 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1300 
GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0503154894 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Four deputies of the Democratic Left Alliance [SLD] 
who did not adhere to the whip applied by this parliamentary 
club in the vote on the budget [today] and voted against the law 
have been deprived of their membership in the club. These 
deputies are: Piotr Ikonowicz, Andrzej Lipski, Cezary 
Mizejewski, and Sranislaw Wisniewski [sitting, respectively, for 
the Lublin, Warsaw, Warsaw, and Warsaw multimember 
constituencies]. There are currently 167 deputies in the 
Democratic Left Alliance [SLD] parliamentary club in the Sejm. 

</TEXT>

