<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Solidarity Outlines Nationwide Strike Protests </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0703143994 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1000 
GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0703143994 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Slupsk heat and power generating plant and the 
timber enterprise in Slawno are the first to join the Solidarity 
nationwide protest action announced for today. 
  Solidarity National Commission Spokesman Piotr Zak told us 
that strikes could also start in other parts of Poland. The 
strike that is just starting will circulate to cover selected 
regions, industries, and enterprises. The nationwide strike 
will take place in the metal and mining industries and on the 
railways. 
  The Solidarity spokesman, who was the guest of the morning 
program on Radio Lodz, said that the railways would go on strike 
on Thursday or Friday. If the strike on the railways is 
repeated, only freight trains will be stopped. Piotr Zak also 
said the the Solidarity power industry section decided that 
state administration buildings and enterprises owing money to 
the power industry will be the first to have their electricity 
cut off. 

</TEXT>

