<H3> <TI>   President Meets With Georgia's Shevardnadze </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0603133594 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1200 
GMT 6 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0603133594 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Georgian President Eduard Shevardnadze made a brief 
stopover in Prague today on his way to an official visit to the 
United States. More from our reporter David Stahlavsky. 
  [Stahlavsky] Vaclav Havel received the Georgian president 
for 
an approximately hour-long meeting at Prague Castle and welcomed 
this opportunity to discuss bilateral relations. For example, 
Georgia will open an embassy in Prague that will also deal with 
other Central European countries. For its part, the Czech 
Republic will open a Consulate General in Tbilisi, and both 
diplomatic representations will be preparing a system of 
treaties to secure wider cooperation. At their meeting, both 
presidents exchanged their views on the situation in Georgia, 
which is being troubled by civil and ethnic war, in Russia, and 
in other parts of the world. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

