<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   No Plan To Apply for EU Membership </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0403170794 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1100 
GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0403170794 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Czech Republic does not intend to apply 
officially for admission to the European Union [EU] in the 
coming months. This was announced by foreign Ministry spokesman 
Vit Kurfurst. He added that the Czech Republic will apply when 
conditions for its successful integration into this structure 
have been achieved. 
  Speaking about Hungary's decision to officially apply for 
full EU membership, which was announced in Budapest yesterday, 
the spokesman said that this is a sovereign decision, and the 
Czech Foreign Ministry will not comment on it in any way. 

</TEXT>

