<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Air Force Faculty Opens at Brno Academy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0403154794 Prague LIDOVE NOVINY in Czech 2 Mar 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU0403154794 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague LIDOVE NOVINY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by "(ivh)": "An Air Force Faculty Has Opened in </F>
Brno"] 
  [Text] Brno--A new Air Force and Air Defense Faculty was 
opened yesterday at the Military Academy in Brno. According to 
the Academy's spokesman, Major Pavel Pazdera, pilots, aircraft 
technical specialists, and airfield servicing staff will be 
trained at the faculty. Graduates receive an electronic-based 
education that can also be applied at civilian airports. The 
faculty's establishment comes as a result of the reorganization 
of the Academy and of the requirements for training aircraft 
specialists for the Czech Army. The only military Air Force 
college in the former CSFR was in Kosice. 

</TEXT>

