<H3> <TI>   Meciar on Decisions of HZDS Council </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0503201094 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1730 GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0503201094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1730 GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Republican Council of the Movement for a 
Democratic Slovakia [HZDS] held a session in Trnava. Its 
members discussed preparations for early parliamentary and local 
elections and elected new officials of the Movement's council. 
The final briefing was attended by newly elected Chairman Arpad 
Matejka and HZDS Chairman Vladimir Meciar. Peter Toman, 
representing our Radiozurnal, interviewed them. 
  [Begin recording] [Toman] Mr. Chairman, what in your view 
are 
the most important conclusions reached at today's session of the 
Council? 
  [Meciar] In substance, a decision was made to form working 
groups to work on the final draft of the Movement's 
program--that is, our election program--which we expect to turn 
subsequently into our government program. 
  The other important thing was the election of the bodies of 
the Council: new Chairman Arpad Matejka and new Deputy Chairman 
Zlocha. Mr. Mihalik continues to be the secretary. They were 
elected by secret ballot in several rounds. 
  The third thing I consider important is that the strategy of 
two options has been more or less drafted: either to go three 
times to election ballot boxes--i.e., a referendum and major 
elections and small elections [not further explained]--or just 
to have the two elections. These issues were drafted and agreed 
upon, and I think that everybody is [word indistinct] going to 
work on them. 
  [Toman] Did you discuss preparations for local elections, 
too? 
  [Meciar] Yes, the selection of candidates and coalition 
strategy is a matter for local bodies. [passage omitted] [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

