<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cease-Fire Marked by Violations Near Borders </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0603163694 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 6 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0603163694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Danko Peric from Knin] </F>
  [Text] The third extension of the cease-fire agreement 
reached by Krajina and Croatia is also marked by violations in 
the border regions. The Croatian Army carried out attacks 
toward the Gracac part of Mount Velebit and infiltrated a 
subversive group in the Teslingrad front. According to the 
general staff of the Serbian army of Krajina, the Croatian 
subversive group that was infiltrated north of Teslingrad in 
Lika was neutralized. 
  In the last 24 hours, the Croatian Army carried out attacks 
with infantry weapons and tanks on Zitnik near Drnis, Otisic in 
the Vrlika region, and the free part of the village of Kasic 
near Benkovac. 
  It was somewhat quieter around Otocac, where the Krajina and 
the Croatian commissions for exchange of war prisoners and other 
humanitarian issues met under the auspices of UNPROFOR [UN 
Protection Forces]. They agreed on the next exchange, which will 
take place in 15 days, and exhumation at several hitherto 
unknown locations where soldiers and civilian victims of the war 
are buried. They also agreed that exchange include the persons 
who, as stated, committed classical types of crime. This 
cooperation under the mediation of foreign observers is thus 
assuming a new quality. 

</TEXT>

