<H3> <TI>   Krajina Serb Forces Recapture Lisac Elevation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0503153094 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0503153094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Danko Peric from Knin] </F>
  [Text] The press center of the general staff of the Serbian 
army of Krajina issued a communique on the situation on the 
battlefields in the last 24 hours stating that the Croatian 
forces, which temporarily captured the Lisac elevation in Lika 
yesterday, have been pushed out. The Lisac elevation had been 
under UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] control until yesterday. 
In contrast to the Croatian fighters, who tried to carry out 
yet another attack in the zone under the UN protection -- which 
was thwarted -- the members of the Serbian army of Krajina did 
not suffer any casualties in the counterattack. 
  The violation of the cease-fire agreement by the Croatian 
Army is again taking place in Lika, mainly around Teslingrad and 
Plasko, where they used infantry weapons. 
  Milan Martic, president of the republic of Serbian Krajina, 
sent greetings to the wounded on 5 March, the day of the wounded 
of the latest war. Our care for the wounded is permanent. No 
one should forget you, the Krajina president said. The meeting 
with the wounded was organized by the people working for the 
Captain Dragan Fund. 

</TEXT>

