<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serb Attacks on HVO Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0603150994 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1400 GMT 6 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0603150994 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Serb aggressors have continued an offensive on 
the Usora area (northern Bosnia), the local command of the 
Croatian Defense Council [HVO] reported on Sunday. The Serb 
forces fired three howitzer shells at civilian targets in the 
village of Jelah destroying several residential buildings on 
Sunday morning, the same source said. The HVO units managed to 
repel a severe artillery-supported infantry attack of the Serb 
aggressors in the area of Glavasi-Kriz-Komin on the western part 
of the Usora battlefield last night, whereas on the eastern part 
of the crisis area the Serb forces failed to carry out an 
infantry breakthrough in the region of 
Cerici-Razbjenjak-Makljanovac at the same time. The enemy 
forces opened antiaircraft weaponry and mortar fire all the 
night on the Usora battlefield, said the same source. Thus far 
one HVO soldier has been reported to be gravely wounded. The HVO 
reconnaissance troops noticed last night a concentration of the 
Serb aggressors' forces and artillery on the western part of the 
Usora battlefield. Another offensive of the enemy formations is 
being expected last few days. 

</TEXT>

