<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs Fire at French UN Troops in Sarajevo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0603120194 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 1100 
GMT 6 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0603120194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] We've just heard that French UN troops again came 
under attack last night in Sarajevo in what they described as a 
deliberate Serb attack. Luc Lemonnier has this report from 
Sarajevo: 
  [Lemonnier] The incident once again took place at the Jewish 
cemetery, close to the center of Sarajevo, in the hills where 
Serbs and Muslims are separated by only a few dozen meters. A 
detachment of French UN troops is also in this frontline sector. 
Earlier in the week they had already returned fire against the 
Serbs with their heavy machine-guns. Last night, just after 
2000, they were the targets of deliberate fire, which a 
high-ranking UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] official said came 
from Bosnian Serb lines. The French soldiers returned fire for 
a few minutes with their machine guns, and one French soldier 
was injured by splinters of stone during the clash. Such 
incidents are a daily occurrence in Sarajevo, especially in the 
evening, and Generals Cot and Rose warned two days ago that 
without a significant increase in UN troop numbers, such 
incidents could end up threatening the cease-fire and the whole 
peace process. 

</TEXT>

