<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Chetniks' Continue Heavy Offensive on Bihac </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0603195494 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1800 GMT 6 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0603195494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Bihac area is stoically resisting a heavy 
chetnik offensive. The enemy's long-range artillery has not been 
quiet today, the 28th day of the aggressor's offensive against 
the Bihac region. Artillery and tank attacks on the defense 
lines on Hacin Vrh and Vrsak and on Cazin have intensified since 
midday. The chetniks also launched fresh attacks on the Grmusa 
plateau, where fierce fighting is under way as I am filing this 
report. 
  At the same time artillery attacks on the fringes of Cazin 
have been intensified. Several howitzer shells have fallen in 
the area of the town while the suburbs on the right bank of the 
river Una have been continuously shelled all day. According to 
unofficial reports there are several casualties. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

