<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Many Civilian Casualties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0703120694 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1100 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0703120694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mirza Sadikovic from Bihac] </F>
  [Text] The attacks by chetnik howitzers, tanks, and mortars 
of all calibers on the lines of defenders in the part of the 
front around Bihac and on Grmusko-Srbljanski Plateau have 
continued throughout the night and up to this moment. Fierce 
battles were fought on the Grmusko-Srbljanski Plateau early this 
morning, where, after ferocious artillery preparation, the 
chetniks considerably intensified attacks on all lines. 
  The defenders -- members of the 5th Corps of the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Army -- responded adamantly, defending every 
inch of territory. Following the established scenario, the 
Serbian aggressor also intensified artillery attacks on Bihac 
and Cazin and their outskirts. 
  There have been many injured and killed civilians in this 
savage artillery attack on Bihac; however, due to current 
hellish situation in this town and throughout the entire Bihac 
district, we do not have definitive reports about this. At the 
time of reporting, fierce shelling of the settlements on the 
right bank of Una River and of the two aforementioned towns is 
underway. 

</TEXT>

