<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Crvenkovski Favors Talks, Goodwill Gestures </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0503203294 Athens ET-1 Television Network in Greek 1900 
GMT 5 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0503203294 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens ET-1 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ET-1 correspondent Dhimitrios Dheliolanis] </F>
  [Text] The 10 members of the Central European Initiative, 
which includes Italy, Austria and eight Eastern European 
countries, expressed here in Trieste, Italy, their deep concern 
about Greece's measures against Skopje [The Former Yugoslav 
Republic of Macedonia--FYROM]. At the same time, they called on 
both sides to continue negotiations in the United Nations. 
Following the end of the two-day ministerial meeting, Skopje 
Foreign Minister Stevo Crvenkovski expressed his satisfaction 
with the communique and repeated his desire for dialogue with 
Greece. Asked if a goodwill gesture can be expected from 
Skopje, Crvenkovski replied: 
  [Begin recording, in English] [Crvenkovski] I think that our 
position is quite clear. We are absolutely for them and for 
continuing negotiations. We favor developing good relations 
between the two countries and we are strongly interested in 
obtaining good relations with.... 
  [Dheliolanis, interrupting] There will be some goodwill 
gesture on your part? 
  [Crvenkovski] There have been many goodwill gestures in the 
past few years and I think that now is the time to sit together 
at the table and continue negotiations in New York. I think the 
only way to solve any problems between the two countries is to 
sit together and talk. [end recording] 
  The Skopje minister, however, avoided answering a question 
about the thinking that led his country to adopt the Sun of 
Veryina as a symbol. Finally, in an interview with a local 
newspaper today, Italian Foreign Minister Beniamino Andreatta 
said that he does not worry about Greece's anger with the 
planned transportation axis north of Greece. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

