<H3> <TI>   Turkey Agrees to Food Aid, Payment to Fund </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0303212094 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0303212094 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Over $2 Million Aid"] </F>
  [Text] Turkey approved of an irretrievable aid for 
Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] 
of 10,000 tons of corn. This month, Turkey will also pay the 
promised $1 million on the account of the fund for settling the 
Macedonian debt toward the World Bank. The Macedonian 
Government delegation, during its yesterday visit to Turkey, 
reached an agreement for purchasing 30,000 tons of wheat and 
20,000 tons of corn. They also agreed to speed up the procedure 
of getting a $1.5 million credit from the Eksim Bank. 

</TEXT>

