<H3> <TI>   Russia's Zhirinovskiy Held at Ljubljana Airport </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0703103494 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 0943 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0703103494 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ljubljana, 7 Mar (TANJUG) -- The leader of the 
Liberal Democratic Party of Russia, Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, who, 
it has been learned, arrived in Slovenia this morning, has been 
held at Ljubljana's Brnik airport. 
  Slovene authorities are not allowing Zhirinovskiy to enter 
the country although the leader of the Russian Liberal Democrats 
has a valid diplomatic passport of the Russian Federation. 
  It is not clear whether the Slovene authorities will deny 
Zhirinovskiy entry, or whether they will let him stay, as is 
claimed, for a private visit to Slovenia. 

</TEXT>

