<H3> <TI>   May Be Deported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0703102194 Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network in Slovene 
1000 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0703102194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovene </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, leader of the Russian 
Liberal Democratic Party, arrived from Moscow at Ljubljana 
airport on an Adria Airways aircraft last night. Together with 
his three companions, he was forced to spent the night at the 
airport as the Slovene immigration officials would not allow him 
entry. 
  In light of the experiences of his latest visit, 
Zhirinovskiy 
is supposedly persona non grata in our country. Zhirinovskiy 
lodged a protest with the immigration organs, while the Russian 
Embassy in Ljubljana has not reacted so far. 
  The Slovene border officials would not allow members of the 
press to come in contact with Zhirinovskiy. He is supposed to 
return to Moscow at 1355 today on a regular flight of the 
Russian carrier Aeroflot. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

