<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Denies 4th Army Commander Replaced </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0403132594 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1100 GMT 4 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0403132594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lieutenant General Niculae Spiroiu, Romanian 
national defense minister, in a statement to our reporters 
today, has denied the report published by the AR-PRESS news 
agency according to which General Paul Cheler had been replaced 
as commander of the 4th [Transylvanian] Army. 
  Spiroiu said that General Cheler is still commander of that 
army and there are no problems whatsoever. This report is 
false, the defense minister asserted, after which he assessed 
that such misleading information is also intended to create an 
unfavorable atmosphere around the leadership of the ministry. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

