<H3> <TI>   HVO Implements Agreement for Weapon Withdrawal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0703152594 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1400 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0703152594 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] By 1200 the HVO [Croatian Defense Council] units had 
fully implemented the agreement between [Bosnian Croat army 
commander] General Roso and [Bosnian Army commander General 
Rasim] Delic. Under the agreement, all heavy weapons of more 
than 12.7-mm caliber are to be placed under control of UNPROFOR 
[UN Protection Forces] or redeployed at an agreed distance from 
the line of separation. Part of the weapons have been moved to 
the agreed location, which is under the control of UNPROFOR and 
HVO soldiers, while the other location is under HVO control 
only. After 1200 UNPROFOR members began a tour of artillery 
positions and the line of separation, HVO spokesman Veso Vegar 
has reported. 

