<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Departure of Canadians Blocked </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0703164794 Montreal Radio Canada International in English 
1430 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0703164794 </F>
<F P=104>  Montreal Radio Canada International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Bosnia's Muslim leaders are trying to end the 
protest against the departure of Canadian peacekeepers from 
Srebrenica. The Canadians have ended their tour of duty in the 
mainly Muslim enclave (?and been relieved) by Dutch troops. But 
protesting Muslims kept the Canadians from leaving their 
compound this weekend. The Muslims see the Canadians as their 
protectors and don't want them to leave. 
  The departure of the Canadians is also being blocked by 
Serbs 
surrounding Srebrenica. They claim the Canadians' heavy-duty 
vehicles will tear up the road and are preventing a UN convoy 
sent from Visoko from reaching the area. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

