<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tudjman Shuffles Military Officer Posts </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802195394 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1600 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2802195394 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Republic of Croatia President Franjo Tudjman has 
passed a decision relieving Brigadier Stjepan Hadanic of his 
duty as assistant defense minister and appointing him head of 
the Military Office of the President, it has been announced from 
the president's office. Franjo Tudjman also relieved Brigadier 
Mile Cuk of his duty as military aide to the president, and 
appointed him commander of the 1st Croatian Guards Corps. 
Franjo Tudjman also relieved Brigadier Kresimir Kaspar of his 
duty as head of the Military Office of the President, and 
appointed him military aide to the president. 

</TEXT>

