<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Granic in Talks With Swedish Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0703192894 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1800 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0703192894 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mate Granic, deputy prime minister and foreign 
minister of the Republic of Croatia, today received Margaretha 
af Ugglas, foreign minister of the Kingdom of Sweden. 
  Foreign Minister Granic briefed the Swedish foreign minister 
on the negotiations which resulted in the signing of the 
Croat-Muslim agreements in Washington, on the contents of the 
signed documents, and on the work of the joint committee in 
Vienna, which is drafting several agreements envisaged by the 
Washington agreement. 
  Foreign Minister Granic thanked the Kingdom of Sweden for 
its 
substantial humanitarian aid, for accepting large numbers of 
refugees, and for the participation of Swedish units in the UN 
peacekeeping operation in the occupied parts of the Republic of 
Croatia. 
  Foreign Minister Margaretha af Ugglas expressed the Swedish 
Government's satisfaction with the Washington agreements and 
pledged support for the peace process and aid for the 
reconstruction of the Republic of Croatia. She invited Granic 
to visit Sweden. It was agreed that Granic will visit Sweden in 
the second half of March. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

