<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Krajina Fighters Claim Success on Gospic Front </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0703165594 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0703165594 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Danko Peric] </F>
  [Text] For the third day in a row, the majority of entries 
in the bulletin of the Serbian Krajina army press center refers 
to the activities of Krajina fighters in expelling Croatian 
combatants who had attacked a section of the region of 
Teslingrad in Lika. This morning, the report that the Cupovac 
region has been regained was confirmed. Yesterday's report said 
that what is in fact involved is the area between Jurkovic and 
(Bartic) Poljana, which was briefly occupied by the Croatian 
combatants. UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] troops should have 
control over it, as was precisely stated in the Vance plan. 
  The headquarters of the Serbian Krajina army has announced 
the liberation of the (?facility) of (Trlo), also on the 
Teslingrad front. In the battles, Krajina fighters suffered no 
losses, but Croatian losses are claimed to be great. It is 
interesting to note that Croatian radio does not report on these 
battles, but has even carried reports that it is allegedly calm 
on the Gospic front. 
  According to the press center of the Serbian Krajina army 
headquarters, there have also been some Croatian Army 
provocations on the (Plascan) section of the Lika front, and 
attacks on Kricko and Zitnic near Drnis, as well as Otesic in 
the Vrlika region. These provocations by the Croatian Army drew 
a response. 

</TEXT>

