<H3> <TI>   Oil Leakage Reported in Northern Border Area </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0703162194 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1200 
GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0703162194 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] A whole system of submersible walls has had to be 
built against oil leakages at River Olse in the border area from 
Jablunkov in the direction of Bohumin. More from our reporter 
Frantisek Tvrz, who is in the affected area: 
  [Tvrz] At the moment, investigators and ecology inspectors 
are investigating how many tonnes of the crude oil product 
leaked from the fuel area of the Czech railways at Jablunkov 
yesterday. According to this morning's statement by the 
breakdown commission, the nonspecialist estimates suggest a 
leakage of approximately six to seven tonnes. 
  The whole system of submersible walls was built immediately 
below Jablunkov but also at the brook at Navsi and then lower 
down, toward the confluence of the Olse border river to the Odra 
River, via Trinec, Cesky Tesin up to Bohumin-Vernovice. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

