<H3> <TI>   Bank Officials Negotiate Japan Exim Bank Loan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0703231194 Bratislava STV 1 Television Network in Slovak 
1830 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0703231194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava STV 1 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Slovak National Bank Governor Vladimir Masar and 
Marian Jusko, vice governor of the bank, returned from Japan 
today. The main aim of their trip was signing an agreement with 
the Exim Bank of Japan about the loan to the value of 
approximately $42 million. 
  The first installment of this loan will be transferred to 
Slovakia as early as 9 March. It will be used for the support 
of small-scale and medium businesses. The first repayment of 
the loan has been set for 15 February 1998. 
  Representatives of the National Bank of Slovakia also held 
talks with the Japanese bank about the possibility of support in 
financing large investment projects. They include, above all, 
development of railway and river transport, development of the 
Bratislava airport, and transportation of gas and oil. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

