<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy Denied Entry; Leaves for Moscow </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0703161794 Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network in Slovene 
1430 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0703161794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovene </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President of the Russian Liberal Democratic Party 
Vladimir Zhirinovskiy at 1400 departed from Ljubljana airport on 
a regular flight by the Russian air carrier Aeroflot to Moscow. 
  Because the Slovene authorities did not allow him entry into 
the country, he spent the night at the airport, together with 
his three companions. He was visited by Yuri Girenko, charge 
d'affaires of the Russian Federation Embassy in Ljubljana. 
  The Slovene Foreign Ministry has reported that it did not 
allow entry to Zhirinovskiy because of violations of public law 
and order during his visit in Slovenia at the end of January. 
On that occasion the Foreign Ministry merely advised him to 
leave the territory of the Republic of Slovenia as soon as 
possible. 

</TEXT>

