<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Profile of SLD Deputy Prime Minister Candidate </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0703193994 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1500 
GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0703193994 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Professor of Economics Dariusz Rosati is the 
official candidate of the Democratic Left Alliance [SLD] to the 
post of deputy prime minister and finance minister. Journalists 
were informed about this decision by the Alliance's press 
spokesman, Zbigniew Siemiatkowski. 
  [Reporter] The SLD leadership and that of the Polish Peasant 
Party, at a joint session on Saturday, gave their support to the 
candidature of Prof. Rosati, Zbigniew Siemiatkowski said. The 
deciding factors were the qualifications of the candidate, his 
wide experience, and the fact that he is well known in 
international economic circles. 
  On Saturday afternoon, the Alliance leader, Aleksander 
Kwasniewski, sent a letter regarding this matter to Prime 
Minister Waldemar Pawlak. The prime minister is in touch with 
our candidate, Siemiatkowski said. 
  Prof. Rosati has spent the past few days in Warsaw. He is at 
present in Geneva, where, for the past three years, he has been 
working as an expert for the United Nations at the European 
Economic Commission. 
  Prof. Rosati is to return to Warsaw at the end of the week, 
Zbigniew Siemiatkowski said. 
  Now a few words about the candidate: He is in his forties, 
is not a member of any party, and had been a member of the 
Polish United Workers Party until its dissolution. He comes 
from Radom. He is married, with two children, and has 
outstanding qualifications and abilities for these posts, 
Zbigniew Siemiatkowski stressed. 

</TEXT>

