<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Steelworks Stage Solidarity-Led Strikes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0803113994 Warsaw PAP in Polish 0919 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0803113994 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Katowice, 8 Mar--A two-hour warning strike was 
organized on Tuesday by the Independent Self-Governing Trade 
Union [NSZZ] Solidarity Steelworks National Division [SKH NSZZ 
Solidarity] as part of a nationwide Solidarity protest action, 
Wlodzimierz Lewandowski, deputy chairman of the SKH NSZZ 
Solidarity, told PAP. 
  Lewandowski said that the strikes were taking place in a 
variety of forms. The protest action is to draw attention to 
the financial problems of employees and their families. The 
teams from the raw material departments have not discontinued 
the technological processes so as not to make the financial 
situation of their steelworks even worse. The strike action has 
been joined by the workers of the Bankowa, Zawiercie, Baildon, 
Batory, Bobrek, and 1 Maja steelworks, among others. At the 
Katowice steelworks, the protest action had been limited to 
collecting money for the strike fund, Renata Bytomska, the 
steelworks press spokeswoman, told PAP. 

</TEXT>

