<H3> <TI>   Serb Policeman Kills Ethnic Albanian </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0703182694 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1435 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0703182694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Pristina, 7 Mar (TANJUG)--Slavisa Nikolic, a trainee 
policeman, killed Faik Maljoku and wounded Bejzak Dzevat after a 
short argument in a restaurant in Kosovo Polje, a TANJUG 
reporter learned today from the regional prosecution office in 
Pristina. 
  According to the reports from the prosecution office, 
Officer 
Nikolic fired two bullets from his service gun at Maljoku, who 
died in a Pristina hospital soon afterwards. Dzevat, who was 
injured during the shooting incident, is stable. Nikolic has 
been detained. An official investigation is under way. 

</TEXT>

