<F P=100> ALBANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meksi Views Army Reform, Military Cooperation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0403190894 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1900 
GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0403190894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana TVSH Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Albanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Promotion, graduation, and oath-taking 
ceremonies for new officers and the start of school activity at 
the Defense Academy of the Republic of Albania were held in one 
of the halls of the Military Academy this morning. [passage 
omitted] 
  Prime Minister Meksi conveyed the greetings of Sali Berisha, 
president of the Republic and commander general, to those 
present. He wished them success in their new, sacred task of 
defending the country. Among other things, Meksi said: 
  [Begin Meksi recording] Today is a remarkable day for you 
and the Army. Your promotion and graduation, as well the start 
of the school process in the Defense Academy, which is 
completely reformed and restructured, constitute an important 
achievement. All this is being held at a historic moment of 
special importance, at a time when real democracy is being 
consolidated in our country and when, on the international 
level, Albania's position has been improved and recognized 
through its numerous education activities in many important 
international institutions. 
  Consequently, even our Army, with its reformation, has 
already broken the framework of long isolation by cooperating 
with many armies of Western and other democratic countries, thus 
aiming to be converted into a qualitative, modern, and 
contemporary army. These prospects become more certain due to 
the approach to NATO as well as the signing of the Partnership 
for Peace initiative, which will naturally integrate Albania 
into the bosom of the NATO alliance. However, the road to 
membership passes through the difficult but indispensable road 
of efficiency, increased military and contemporary knowledge, 
high discipline, and a very high state of alertness. [end 
recording] [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

