<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs Continue Attacks on Maglaj, Bihac, Cazin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0703163894 </F>
<F P=103> AU0703163894 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina 
Network in Serbo-Croatian at 1400 GMT on 7 March carries within 
its regular 30-minute newscast several reports on the combat 
situation in the republic: 
  According to Maglaj correspondent Hajrudin Cermic, "instead 
of a cease-fire arranged to exchange the dead bodies of the 
soldiers of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army and those of the Serbian 
aggressor, Maglaj is being subjected to artillery fire. After 
unsuccessful attacks on [words indistinct], the attacks were 
directed exclusively on civilian targets. Some 70 57-mm shells 
were fired from Bofors, while tanks are opening intermittent 
fire from [name indistinct]. One civilian was wounded." 
  Correspondent Mirudin Aldobasic reports from the 7th South 
Operations Group that "the aggressor early this morning suddenly 
shelled with heavy artillery Kalosevici and the lines of defense 
of the 207th Brcko Brigade and [word indistinct]. The shelling 
is continuing, although infantry attacks have been successfully 
repelled." Aldobasic also says that "the aggressor is 
constantly" attacking defense lines in the Teslic region with 
heavy arms. 
  Reporting on the shelling of Bihac, correspondent Mirza 
Sadikovic says that "one shell alone killed three and wounded 
five persons while they were performing their duties and jobs. 
Regarding the new material damage, no one is talking about it 
any longer. The final number of the victims of today's shelling 
is still unfortunately unknown, considering that the killing 
from the hills around Bihac is still going on. In addition to 
Bihac, Cazin and the surrounding area are also being targeted 
with howitzers and mortars." 
  Zavidovici correspondent Viktor Boban reports that "the 
chetniks this afternoon launched attacks on the defense lines in 
several sectors." He also says that the "defenders are fiercely 
responding, not allowing the aggressor to advance even a 
millimeter." 
  Boban concludes his report by saying that three civilians 
have been killed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

