<H3> <TI>   Berov Suffers Heart Attack; Matinchev Named </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0803151594 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1500 
GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0803151594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At the start of the news, I will repeat once again 
the announcement from the Council of Ministers Press Center: 
  At 2 AM on 8 March, Prime Minister Lyuben Berov suffered a 
heart attack, following which he was admitted to the Lozenets 
Hospital of the Military Medical Academy in Sofia. After the 
doctors had held a consultation, it was decided that it was 
necessary to admit him for in-patient treatment. 
  It was announced later that Deputy Prime Minister Evgeni 
Matinchev will fulfill the duties of prime minister while 
Professor Berov is undergoing medical treatment. 

</TEXT>

